     1                          ; Code to relocate the Ozmoo executable down in memory. This is used on some
     2                          ; Acorn builds to allow the executable to load high and then move itself down
     3                          ; to an optimal address for the machine it's running on.
     4                          ;
     5                          ; The relocation model is very simple and relies on building two versions of the
     6                          ; code starting at different page-aligned addresses, then comparing them to see
     7                          ; which bytes need to be offset to compensate for the relocation at runtime.
     8                          ; This works pretty well in practice, but it means that code can't vary in
     9                          ; "complex" ways depending on where it's being assembled - e.g. it's OK to do
    10                          ; "lda #>.story_start" but "lda #($80->.story-start)" will cause an error when
    11                          ; generating the relocations as the two versions will differ but in an unexpected
    12                          ; way.
    13                          
    14                          !zone {
    15                          
    16                          reloc_start = program_start
    17                          !if <reloc_start != 0 {
    18                              !error "reloc_start must be on a page boundary"
    19                          }
    20                          ; When relocating acorn-cache.asm on the host we will use these zero page
    21                          ; locations. I can't find any official documentation to say what zero page we
    22                          ; can and can't use, but looking at the different versions of the tube host code
    23                          ; on mdfs.net I can't see any problem with transient use of these in practice.
    24                          .delta = $70
    25                          .codep = $71 ; 2 bytes
    26                          .deltap = $73 ; 2 bytes
    27                          .count = $75 ; 2 bytes
    28                          .src = $77 ; 2 bytes
    29                          .dst = $79 ; 2 bytes
